    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/korean-skincare-uk/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_ARTICLE&editorId=602061125860721342&sectionId=602061125911052990)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggSeD_5BpRe_text","label":"ggSeD_5BpRe_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#gLdNijixX9\"><span style=\"color:#FFC5E1;\">Introduction</span></a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRtqxKFh4j_text","label":"ggRtqxKFh4j_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#gpr5SSXJ2-\">What are ceramides?</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDWYk8HtfY_text","label":"ggDWYk8HtfY_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#gt-MbnaTNx\">Who should use ceramides in winter?</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUqM5Vr3_s_text","label":"ggUqM5Vr3_s_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#gedz2dV3ky\">Pairing ceramides with active ingredients</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUmnVPmtOQ_text","label":"ggUmnVPmtOQ_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#gelcRB4fFv\">Daily use for lasting results</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5kJYHdrai_text","label":"gg5kJYHdrai_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#g0gDAlPvAx\">Our favourite products</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggA5hgLkFwW_text","label":"ggA5hgLkFwW_text","default":"<p><a href=\"#goUE24q9Y7\">Final thoughts</a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsuc8uMOvV_text","label":"ggsuc8uMOvV_text","default":"<p><i>Hey SkinTalks readers! In this SkinTalks blog, we’re going to talk about Ceramides.</i><br><br><i>We’ve all experienced it, that tight, dry feeling when our skin seems to be fighting against us, no matter how much moisturizer we apply. Most of the time, the problem isn’t that we’re using the wrong products; it’s that our skin doesn’t have enough ceramides.</i><br><br><i>In this blog, we’ll explore what ceramides are, why they matter, who benefits most, and highlight some of the best Korean skincare products to help us all achieve resilient, glowing skin.</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoxIGOxvsy_text","label":"ggoxIGOxvsy_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16pt;\">What are ceramides?</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGJGclMkS2_text","label":"ggGJGclMkS2_text","default":"<p><a href=\"$locationOrigin/collections/ceramide\"><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"><i>Ceramides</i></span></a><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"> </span>are a type of lipid (fat molecule) naturally found in our skin that play a crucial role in maintaining a healthy skin barrier. You can think of them as the glue that holds our skin cells together.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcohb9YesS_text","label":"ggcohb9YesS_text","default":"How do ceramides support a healthy skin barrier?"},{"type":"html","id":"ggySfV-BK0U_text","label":"ggySfV-BK0U_text","default":"<p>• Lock in moisture: They prevent water from escaping, keeping skin hydrated.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>• Protect the skin barrier: They act as a shield against environmental stressors like pollution, harsh weather, and irritants.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>• Support skin health: Adequate ceramides make skin look smooth, plump, and resilient.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>When ceramide levels drop, due to aging, harsh climates, or over-cleansing, the skin barrier weakens, leading to dryness, sensitivity, flakiness, or irritation. Using ceramide-rich skincare helps replenish these lipids and restore the skin’s natural protective barrier.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg55aTFZsOj_text","label":"gg55aTFZsOj_text","default":"What happens when your skin lacks ceramides?"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNh_x9P0nP_text","label":"ggNh_x9P0nP_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">We’ve all had that moment when we step out into the cold and feel our skin tighten, itch, or even flake a little. It’s uncomfortable, frustrating, and can make us feel like no cream is strong enough. The truth is, our skin isn’t failing us; it’s just losing ceramides, the natural lipids that keep our skin barrier strong.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">Think of ceramides as tiny bodyguards in our skin. When winter hits, these bodyguards can get depleted, leaving our skin exposed to harsh winds, low humidity, and indoor heating. Without enough ceramides, water escapes, skin feels dry and tight, and irritation sets in.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">By adding ceramide-rich products to our routine, we’re essentially replacing those bodyguards. They lock in moisture, rebuild the protective barrier, and help calm any irritation.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLww0IDH_M_text","label":"ggLww0IDH_M_text","default":"Who should use ceramides in winter?"},{"type":"html","id":"ggAT0Jia7zK_text","label":"ggAT0Jia7zK_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">We all experience winter skin struggles differently, but almost everyone can benefit from ceramides.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">If your skin feels tight, dry, or flaky, it’s a clear sign that your barrier needs a boost. Ceramides help lock in moisture and restore the skin’s natural protective layer.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">Those with sensitivity know how easily redness, irritation, or itching can appear when the weather turns cold. Ceramides act like a calming shield, helping skin stay balanced and comfortable.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">Even </span><a href=\"$locationOrigin/collections/anti-aging\"><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#FD76A9;font-size:16px;\"><i>aging skin</i></span></a><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\"> can benefit, since ceramides help maintain hydration, plump fine lines, and support overall skin resilience.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">And if you’re someone who spends a lot of time in harsh climates or heated indoor spaces, ceramides are your winter hero, reinforcing your skin barrier and keeping your complexion soft, smooth, and happy.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">In short: if your skin feels dry, irritated, or just in need of extra protection, ceramides are for you.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggMUNpCch3i_text","label":"ggMUNpCch3i_text","default":"Pairing ceramides with active ingredients"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcTnLzcbR9_text","label":"ggcTnLzcbR9_text","default":"<p>Ceramides are very flexible and can be used with almost any other skincare ingredient. If you’re using stronger treatments like retinol, exfoliating acids, or <a href=\"$locationOrigin/collections/vitamin-c\"><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"><i>vitamin C</i></span></a>, ceramides help protect your skin and prevent dryness, redness, or irritation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>A simple way to use them: apply your active treatment first, then follow with a ceramide-rich moisturizer or <a href=\"$locationOrigin/collections/serums\"><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"><i>serum</i></span></a>. This soothes and strengthens your skin, letting you get the full benefits of your treatments without harming your skin barrier.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggF25h05gz7_text","label":"ggF25h05gz7_text","default":"Daily use for lasting results"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfLdMNhjyj_text","label":"ggfLdMNhjyj_text","default":"<p>One of the best things about ceramides is that they’re gentle enough for everyday use, making them ideal for building long-term skin resilience. When incorporated consistently into your routine, ceramides help maintain optimal hydration, smooth texture, and a strong protective barrier, which translates to healthier, more balanced skin over time.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>In short, daily ceramide use isn’t just about temporary comfort; it’s an investment in your skin’s long-term health.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggT7M-flqaH_text","label":"ggT7M-flqaH_text","default":"Our favourite products"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoySuQ1J71_text","label":"ggoySuQ1J71_text","default":"<p>Here’s a list of K‑beauty favorites packed with ceramides, perfect for strengthening your skin barrier, boosting hydration, and keeping your skin calm and balanced. Many of these are cult classics loved across all skin types, from dry and <a href=\"$locationOrigin/collections/sensitive-skin\"><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"><i>sensitive</i></span></a><span style=\"color:#FD76A9;\"> </span>to combination and reactive.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnHaGITas-_label","label":"ggnHaGITas-_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4LRmYFE9p_label","label":"gg4LRmYFE9p_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyGmFCLcZW_label","label":"ggyGmFCLcZW_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"gg69zOKQYJg_label","label":"gg69zOKQYJg_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"ggxOMKJeRKx_label","label":"ggxOMKJeRKx_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoCDOALZcG_label","label":"ggoCDOALZcG_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnF0DNqqkZ_label","label":"ggnF0DNqqkZ_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"gg36pxsbhUF_label","label":"gg36pxsbhUF_label","default":"See more"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBGWKX4pzx_text","label":"ggBGWKX4pzx_text","default":"Final thoughts"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRA4cODjof_text","label":"ggRA4cODjof_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">Winter doesn’t have to mean dry, tight, or irritated skin. From our experience, incorporating ceramide-rich products, whether in the form of nourishing creams, hydrating serums, or protective masks, is one of the most effective ways to restore the skin barrier, lock in moisture, and defend your skin against environmental stressors.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">For anyone struggling with dryness, sensitivity, or simply wanting to maintain a healthy, radiant complexion, ceramides are an essential part of a skincare routine. And whenever you might feel confused about products or have questions, the KS team is always here to help.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(35,35,35);font-size:16px;\">Take care, and until next time.</span></p>"}],
